text: Scirpophaga brunnealis is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by George Hampson in 1919. It is found in Myanmar and Nepal. The wingspan is 27–29 mm. The forewings are dull ochreous brown with a dark fuscous spot at the lower angle of the cell. The hindwings are ochreous brown. ==References== Category:Moths described in 1919 Category:Schoenobiinae Category:Moths of Asia
title: Scirpophaga brunnealis
